    {
        "content": "<p>Here is my MWE: <a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/sUoJbKWV0gJnpwRD1mouVxEL/mwe.lean\">mwe.lean</a>. I believe that Lean being unable to solve <code>iN.bitvec_eq_zero_iff</code> is due to Lean not unwrapping <code>OfNat</code>?</p>",
        "id": 538329444,
        "sender_full_name": "l1mey",
        "timestamp": 1757374675
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I edited the question to include the definition of <code>PNat</code> which I accidentally left out. It is:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PNat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">//</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">deriving</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DecidableEq</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 538329796,
        "sender_full_name": "l1mey",
        "timestamp": 1757375009
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Instead of writing a theorem for <code>iN.bitvec_eq_zero_iff</code>, that proves <code>(iN.bitvec b = 0) ↔ (b = 0)</code>, it would be better to make it general and show it for every <code>OfNat</code> literal. However, I wouldn't know how express that.</p>",
        "id": 538330055,
        "sender_full_name": "l1mey",
        "timestamp": 1757375172
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Are you rolling your own PNat, or is this Mathlib's <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=PNat#doc\">docs#PNat</a> and you've extracted it for the mwe? (It's ok importing mathlib for this sort of mwe.)</p>",
        "id": 538330611,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1757375639
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This has been extracted from Mathlib, just a couple lines from the file <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/88928cefd7edb1ba61623bffd4e86389dfe1f648/Mathlib/Data/PNat/Notation.lean#L11-L14\">PNat/Notation.lean</a>. I have decided to roll my own in my code and that is reflected in the MWE.</p>",
        "id": 538330786,
        "sender_full_name": "l1mey",
        "timestamp": 1757375803
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's a quick way to deal with <code>bitvec_eq_zero_iff</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bitvec_zero_eq_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PNat</span><span class=\"o\">):</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bitvec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitVec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bitvec_eq_zero_iff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PNat</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitVec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bitvec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bitvec_zero_eq_zero</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The first lemma could be a simp lemma I think.</p>",
        "id": 538330871,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1757375888
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I found that this theorem solves it in the general case for zero iff:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bitvec_eq_ofNat_iff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PNat</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitVec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bitvec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bitvec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitVec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But this seems quite a bit finicky. Other than that, I am still left with <code>⊢ iN.shlNswClean a✝ b✝ = bitvec a✝</code> in <code>test_without</code> which is a bit tricky.</p>",
        "id": 538331324,
        "sender_full_name": "l1mey",
        "timestamp": 1757376221
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This expresses that theorem using OfNat literals:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofnat_eq_zero_iff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PNat</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">OfNat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofNat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">OfNat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofNat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitVec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bitvec_eq_zero_iff</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It's probably missing <code>no_index</code> annotations around the literals for simp to apply it</p>",
        "id": 538331327,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1757376224
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That is good, I looked around for <code>no_index</code> and found a couple. So I am normalising the <code>iN</code> literal representation and that problem is solved. However, I still want to deal with <code>test_without</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/-- Theorem for normalizing the iN literal representation. -/</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- This will perform rewrites of `0 =&gt; 0 = bitvec (OfNat.ofNat 0)`, which is just a `BitVec` literal.</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ofNat_eq_bitvec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PNat</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">((</span><span class=\"n\">no_index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">OfNat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofNat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bitvec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">no_index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">OfNat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofNat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">solve_current</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PNat</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitVec</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↑</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">no_index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitVec</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofNat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↑</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">no_index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitVec</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofNat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↑</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">test_without</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">):</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">shlNsw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">unfold</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">iN</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">shlNsw</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">split</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">try</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  case h_3</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  n : PNat</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  x✝¹ x✝ : iN n</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  a✝ b✝ : BitVec ↑n</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  heq✝ : 0#↑n = b✝</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  ⊢ iN.shlNswClean a✝ b✝ = bitvec a✝</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  -/</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Still the same issue. I tried to create the <code>solve_current</code> theorem to see if I could get simp to solve this.</p>",
